# Project Prep 1

## Cooperation
1. What are the key strengths of each person on the team?
 - B: team player, project experience, terminal, file storage
 - E: design (CSS), organization, detailed
 - L: vizualization, organizating step to complete a task
 - K: wireframe, structure out tasks needed, presentation skills
 - R: quick learner, presentation skills, keep us moving forward
 
  
2. How can you best utilize these strengths in the execution of your project?
 - B: project planning, tasks, keeping team positive, troubleshooting of code
 - E: availability to put in time on the project, great design, high level of commitment
 - L: long term and short term goals, breaking out tasks
 - K: wireframing, breaking down code
 - R: team player, prepared for task execution
  
3. In which professional competencies do you each want to develop greater strength?
 - B: wireframing, laying out the code structure
 - E: javascript deeper dive
 - L: JavaScript writing out code, professional networking
 - K: JavaScript further reaching goal, catalog "stores of stuff"
 - R: continue to explore JavaScript 

4. Knowing that every person in your team needs to understand all aspects of the project, how do you plan to approach the day-to-day work?
 - B: scrum meeting, use of project planning w/task breakdowns
 - E: pairing, working together, brainstorming
 - L: pair programming, PR approvals spread out
 - K: communicate via standup, reroute, reschedule, re-prioritize work
 - R: standup mtg, keeps everyone working as a team to meet goals, can assist one another
 
